Drop -Werror from cet_set_compiler_flags.

lardataalg builds with DIAGS CAUTIOUS + WERROR. Under GCC 14 / C++20 (the conda
art-stack standard, vs upstream's C++17 default) the stricter diagnostics in the
DetectorInfo/Utilities headers get promoted to hard errors. CXXFLAGS can't demote
cetmodules' add_compile_options(-Werror) (it lands after $CXXFLAGS), so drop the
WERROR keyword. See conda/potential_improvements.md (#2).
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -15,7 +15,6 @@
 cet_cmake_env()

 cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS CAUTIOUS
-  WERROR
   NO_UNDEFINED
   EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic -Wno-unused-local-typedefs
 )
